<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[102,753,281,664]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[140,257,352,376]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Discussion</emphasis>
. – This species shows variation in the number of calyx lobes from five (4+1) to four. The presence of both forms on 
<emphasis box="[206,419,416,440]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Barthelat &amp; al. 386</emphasis>
suggests that the reduced fifth lobe is sometimes lost. Similar variation in the number and configuration of calyx lobes is known for 
<taxonomicName box="[548,631,480,504]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[548,631,480,504]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Justicia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but apparently has not been reported in other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[606,697,512,536]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Anisotes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[606,697,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Anisotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is noteworthy that 
<taxonomicName box="[289,447,544,568]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Himantochilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="comorensis">
<emphasis box="[289,447,544,568]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">A. comorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and at least one Malagasy species (
<taxonomicName authority="T. F. Daniel, Letsara &amp; Martin-Bravo" authorityName="T. F. Daniel, Letsara &amp; Martin-Bravo" box="[200,748,576,600]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Anisotes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="venosus">
<emphasis box="[200,319,576,600]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">A. venosus</emphasis>
T. F. Daniel, Letsara &amp; Martín-Bravo
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="DANIEL, T. F." box="[103,320,608,632]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" pagination="396 - 408" refId="ref5749" refString="DANIEL, T. F., R. LETSARA &amp; S. MARTIN- BRAVO (2013). Four new species of Anisotes (Acanthaceae) from Madagascar. Novon 22: 396 - 408." type="journal article" year="2013">DANIEL &amp; al., 2013</bibRefCitation>
) have a calyx with one lobe somewhat reduced in size relative to the others.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[102,753,680,953]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
The four-aperturate pollen of this species (
<figureCitation box="[574,635,680,704]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[118,143,1873,1893]" captionTargetBox="[120,1493,734,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-268@4.[386,1227,777,1810]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. – Pollen of Anisotes Nees in the Comoros Archipelago. A-B. Anisotes mayottensis T. F. Daniel; C-D. A. comorensis (Lindau) T. F. Daniel; A. Apertural view; B. Interapertural view; C. pertural view; D. Interapertural view. [A-B: Pascal 936, CS; C-D: Humblot 1584, P]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5715288" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5715288/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) is unusual in the genus. It has been previously documented only for the tropical west African species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lindau" authorityName="Lindau" box="[428,655,744,768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Anisotes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guineensis">
<emphasis box="[428,573,744,768]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">A. guineensis</emphasis>
Lindau
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BADEN, C." pageId="9" pageNumber="54" pagination="623 - 664" refId="ref5546" refString="BADEN, C. (1981 b). The genus Anisotes (Acanthaceae), a taxonomic revision. Nordic J. Bot. 1: 623 - 664." type="journal article" year="1981">BADEN, 1981b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
